---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Drive game UI by meaning" description="The official Gua reference for Godot and Unity integration, testing, Inspector, and MCP automation.">
  <section class="hero-home"><div class="inner">
    <span class="kicker">RUNTIME UI AUTOMATION FOR GAMES</span>
    <h1>Drive game UI by <em>meaning</em>.</h1>
    <p>Gua exposes a running game's UI as a semantic tree. Tests and AI agents can find and activate a “Start Game” button by identity and role—without brittle coordinates or image recognition.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="/en/unity/">Read the Unity guide →</a><a class="button secondary" href="/en/docs/">Browse the API docs</a></div>
    <figure class="hero-demo">
      <img src="/gua-hero-demo.webp" alt="An AI agent uses the Gua MCP server to inspect the semantic UI tree and remotely activate the Start Game button in a Godot game" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" />
      <figcaption><span>DEMO</span> An AI agent operates game UI through MCP</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div></section>
  <section class="home-content">
    <span class="kicker">GET THE LATEST</span><h2>Start with the latest release</h2>
    <p>Download the Godot add-on and Windows Inspector from <a href="https://github.com/link1345/gua/releases/latest" style="color:var(--mint);text-decoration:underline">GitHub Releases / Latest</a>. Building Gua from source is intended for contributors working on Gua itself.</p>
    <span class="kicker">HOW IT WORKS</span><h2>Observe the real input path</h2>
    <div class="pipeline"><div><strong>01 / DRAW</strong>The game engine renders UI normally</div><div><strong>02 / REFLECT</strong>The adapter collects semantic state</div><div><strong>03 / CONNECT</strong>The bridge publishes it over WebSocket</div><div><strong>04 / ACT</strong>Tests, Inspector, and MCP operate it</div></div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <a class="chapter-card" href="/en/godot/"><span>ENGINE / 01</span><h3>Godot guide</h3><p>Attach the GDScript adapter, collect the Control tree, and exercise live scenes from external tests.</p></a>
      <a class="chapter-card" href="/en/unity/"><span>ENGINE / 02</span><h3>Unity guide</h3><p>Reflect Unity 6 UI Toolkit, uGUI, and TextMeshPro and test Editor or Player processes externally.</p></a>
      <a class="chapter-card" href="/en/inspector/"><span>TOOL / 02</span><h3>Inspector</h3><p>Diagnose the tree, invoke semantic actions, record/replay, and compare PNGs.</p></a>
      <a class="chapter-card" href="/en/mcp/"><span>TOOL / 03</span><h3>MCP server</h3><p>Expose all semantic actions, Recording, Replay, and visual comparison to AI agents.</p></a>
      <a class="chapter-card" href="/en/docs/"><span>REFERENCE / 04</span><h3>API docs</h3><p>Understand the recommended Godot path, .NET Standard 2.1 support, and separate Visual/Recording packages.</p></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
